(AP Photo/Jim Mone, File)Apparently, NBC didn’t learn there lesson after trying this the first time.
Several weeks ago, Heidi Przybyla pushed a story claiming that a man had died after ingesting chloroquine.
Namely, that the man had taken fish tank cleaner and not any actual medication.
NEW to @NBCNews: Family of New York woman blames hydroxychloroquine combo for fatal heart attack https://t.co/TDIQrAN2lP — Heidi Przybyla (@HeidiNBC) April 16, 2020What’s the real story?
The piece goes on to mention — twice — that Trump touted the drug, and notes that Media Matters says that Fox News touts the drug.